  "text": "Historically, older age within the AYA population independently predicted poor prognosis in treatment for ALL, with 5 year OS falling from 61.4 % in patients aged 15 to 20 years to 44.8 % in young adults aged 20-30 years [CITATION_1] . However, with contemporary therapies administered in pediatric centers, EFS and OS for the AYA subgroup has improved substantially, and has grown increasingly similar amongst all patients over the age of 10 years [23••, 25, 56, 57] .",
